    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Medium model risk. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the single test configuration is the normative ASTM F1717 regulatory standard and FEA predictions are conservative relative to experimental means across all QoIs. E/uval values are below 1.96 and percentage differences below 10% for all primary QoIs. The overall credibility evidence package, including project requirements documentation referenced in factor rationale narratives, is sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim.",
